race.comment: JUSTAFEVER (5) led and won her Maiden comfortably at Lismore over this distance. She will push forward and has plenty of scope for improvement. A decent chance to repeat. PER CAPITA (6) made good improvement placing over 1420m at Lismore. Comes back in grade and can make the finish if the awkward gate is managed. BIANCO NERO (8) has been plainer her last two but the Coffs Harbour form prior reads well enough. She has an inside barrier and deserves to be considered. COWGIRL LILLY (9) has the ability but the barrier is cruel. Expect her to settle back early and be saved for the final crack at them.
